"Okay, using `_repr_image_svg_xml()` seems to do the trick.\n\nThank you for reporting. We will have to see whether we pin 0.18.* for now or make the code work with both 0.18 and 0.19 ...\r\n\r\nOut of curiosity, what work are you using DecayLanguage for?\n\nOr you could also force >=0.19, right?\r\n\r\nI am trying to understand the B-tagging at Belle (II) and using DecayLanguage to study the current MC modeling, to see how well it agrees with PDG, and how it can be further improved. Along the way I made some custom functions like `build_decay_chains_to_inclusive_fsp`, `build_decay_chains_to_specific_fsp` (which identifies all possible intermediate resonances), modified `DecayChainViewer` to show effective BF at fsp level and `DecayChainToTable`.\r\nYou can see some of it in [this example notebook](https://github.com/vvsagar/decaylanguage/blob/inclusive-bf-studies/notebooks/ExampleInclusiveBF.ipynb). I was mostly hacking things for my convinence, but if you think any of this would be useful features, I can optimize and make official PRs."